# Trading-tuned local model — ACCURATE profile.
#
# A heavier Q8 quant for better numerical / reasoning fidelity, paired with a
# smaller 4k context to stay inside the same ~16GB-VRAM budget as the fast
# profile. Prefer this when your prompts fit in 4k and you want the model's
# best answers over raw speed.
#
# Build:   ollama create trading-accurate -f Modelfile.trading-accurate
# Use:     pick provider "ollama" in the CLI, then "Custom model ID" -> trading-accurate
#
# Swap FROM for any base model + quant your Ollama library has and your VRAM fits.
FROM qwen3.5:9b-q8_0

# Smaller context to offset the heavier quant and stay within VRAM.
PARAMETER num_ctx 4096

# Low temperature for run-to-run stability (see the README "Reproducibility" note).
PARAMETER temperature 0.2
PARAMETER top_p 0.9

# Discourage the repetition loops small local models fall into on long reports.
PARAMETER repeat_penalty 1.05

# Cap tokens per turn so a single agent can't stall the graph.
PARAMETER num_predict 2048
